  "preparation": "Chop bread into smallish cubes and put into a large bowl.  Mix together milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla and pour over bread.  mix lighty with wooden spoons.  Add pecans and raisins and add to mixPour pudding into a large, buttered souffle dish and bake for 55 minutes.  Cut edges with sharf knife to unmold.Whiskey sauce:  whisk together ingredients in a saucepan and simmer while stirring constantly until sauce is some thickened.Serve half the sauce over the pudding and arrange the rest in a gravy bowl to be served alongside.",
